This is a benchmarking tool for testing [EIP-1380 Reduced gas cost for call to self ](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1380).
All benchmarks are basd on geth.

## Approach

A scheme with two contracts is used:

Contract `a`:
```
while true:
   call b with all available gas
```

- Contract `b`

```
call b with all available gas
```
This is the resulting genesis alloc:
```json
{
 "0x000000000000000000000000000000000000ff0a": {
  "code": "0x5b6000600060006000600061ff0b5af1600056",
  "balance": "0xffffffff"
 },
 "0x000000000000000000000000000000000000ff0b": {
  "code": "0x5880808080305af1",
  "balance": "0xffffffff"
 }
}
```

This scenario has the following benefits:

- `B` can be heavily optimized, gas-wise,
- The call-tree will go as deep as possible into recursion at `B`, eventually
going out-of-gas on the last call. However, all unused 1/64ths are returned back up the call tree,
all the way back to `A`, which does it again in a loop.

The actual code of `b` is 
```

	DUP1    // out offset
	DUP1    // insize
	DUP1    // inoffset
	DUP1    // value
	ADDRESS // address
	GAS     // Gas

```
